<div class="box-title" style="margin-top: -6px;">
	Frequently asked questions
</div>

<div class="info-box well-box border-box rounded-5 alias-smooth relative">

	<div class="unit">
		<h4>What is mine?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			Mine is a quick and easy service for telling people when you buy something. 
			Post your item's official picture, store and link; control who you share with; and build your online catalog of purchases.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>What do I need to use the service?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			Not much. To 
      <%=link_to_unless @web_view_mode,
          "log in",
          root_path(:src => "faq"),
          :class => "dark underlined"%>
      you need either a Twitter or Facebook account.
			If you want to share your purchases out to Facebook, Twitter and Tumblr, you'll need accounts for these services.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>Who sees the purchases I share?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			Your followers on mine (you'll build these up over time), and, if you connect your accounts, your connections on Facebook, Twitter and Tumblr, too.
			You control who sees what every time you post.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>What does following someone on mine do?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			When you click the 'Follow' button next to a user's name, you'll start seeing purchased items they've shared in your feed when you log in.
			You can follow and unfollow anyone you like, at any time.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>How do I find people to follow?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			If you have someone in mind, you can search for them or invite them to join you. 
			You'll also discover all sorts of interesting people through browsing their purchases, comments and followers.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>Who makes mine?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			We're a small team based in Palo Alto, California. Find out more about us 
      <%=link_to "here",
          about_path(:src => "faq",:web_view_mode => @web_view_mode),
          :class => "dark underlined"%>.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="unit">
		<h4>I have a problem. Whom should I contact?</h4>
		<p class="txt m border-box" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
			Email us any time at <a class="dark underlined" href="mailto:contact@getmine.com">contact@getmine.com</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.
		</p>
	</div>
	
</div>


<%content_for :javascript do%>
  <script type="text/javascript">
    Denwen.Track.action("FAQ View",{"Source" : "<%=@source%>"});
  </script>
<%end unless @web_view_mode%>
